I"Ì<p>Here we will define cylindrical coordinates. If you have learned about polar coordinates in single variable calculus, then this discussion will be a direct extension of polar coordinates to three dimensions. In cylindrical coordinates, the three variables are</p>
<ol>
<li> $r$, the distance from the $z$ axis </li>
<li> $\varphi$, the angle measured in the $xy$ plane from the postiive $x$ axis. </li>
<li> $z$ the height above the $xy$ plane. </li>
</ol>
